main event: A sighting of an unidentified flying object was reported near Duluth, Minnesota on 18 July 1954.
interesting points: The sighting was observed for a duration of 3 minutes,The object was initially considered a balloon but remained unidentified,The pilots determined the object was at an estimated altitude of 45,223 feet,The sighting was conducted by the crew of the 114th Fighter Interceptor Squadron at Duluth Municipal Airport,The report was part of the Project Blue Book documentation.
witness description: Civilian housewives and military personnel including an operations officer and interceptor pilot.
